Description
-----------
Contour is a python utility for extracting contour lines and segmenting 
an image in to layers(bins).

The user may specify the number of layers (or bins) up to a maximum of 9
using the `layercount` flag.

Requirements
------------
- Python 2.7: http://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7/
- Pillow: http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pillow

Python Execution
----------------
python contour.py <input_image> <output_image>
-or-
python contour.py --layercount 2 <input_image> <output_image>


Binary Execution
----------------
contour.exe <input_image> <output_image>
-or-
contour.exe --layercount 2 <input_image> <output_image>